- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on distributed data aggregation algorithms. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the algorithms are used to determine network properties. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses different types of aggregation functions and techniques. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the algorithms can be used to direct the execution of other applications. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as some aggregation algorithms may have security implications.
